text: Yasmeen Khan (born 7 January 1999) is a Namibian cricketer and the current captain of the Namibia women's national cricket team. She made her Women's Twenty20 International (WT20I) debut for Namibia on 20 August 2018, against Malawi, in the 2018 Botswana Cricket Association Women's T20I Series. It was the first WT20I match to be played by Namibia. In August 2019, she was named as the captain of Namibia's squad for the 2019 ICC Women's World Twenty20 Qualifier tournament in Scotland. She played in Namibia's opening match of the tournament, on 31 August 2019, against Ireland. She was the leading run-scorer for Namibia in the tournament, with 55 runs in five matches. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1999 births Category:Living people Category:Namibian women cricketers Category:Namibia women Twenty20 International cricketers Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
